quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  67,27,"But when they saw it approaching, the faces of those who had denied turned gloomy, and it was said, “This is what you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>used to <span class=""h"">claim<sup foot_note=""81350"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><i class=""s"">(would never happen) </i>.”"
  67,28,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Have you seen: if Allah makes me and those with me perish or has mercy on us, who then will protect the deniers from a painful punishment?”"
  67,29,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “He is the All-Merciful; we have attained faith in Him, and in Him alone we have placed our trust, and soon <span class=""h"">you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><span class=""h"">will know<sup foot_note=""81351"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>who is in evident misguidance.”"
  67,30,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>seen:if your water drains away, who then will bring you pure running water?”"
  68,1,"Nûn. By the pen and all that they inscribe."
  68,2,"Your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord’s blessing does not make you a madman."
  68,3,"And most surely, for you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>is an unfailing reward."
  68,4,"And very truly, you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are of great moral character."
  68,5,"Thus you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>shall see and they shall see"
  68,6,"which of you is the demented."
  68,7,"Indeed, your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord is He Who knows better who has strayed from His way, and it is He Who knows better of the rightly guided."
  68,8,"So do not obey the disbelievers;"
  68,9,"they would like you to compromise, then they too would compromise."
  68,10,"And do not obey any despicable swearer,"
  68,11,"backbiter, spreader of malicious gossip,"
  68,12,"preventer of good, transgressor, sinful,"
  68,13,"brutal; moreover, of spurious parentage!"
  68,14,"<span class=""h"">Just<sup foot_note=""81352"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>because he has money and sons,"
  68,15,"when Our signs{1}are read to him, he says, “Legends of the ancients!”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used isayat(singularayah). Ayahmeans ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Quran,like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose.Each such unit isconsidered a ‘sign’from God.
